Description: P pilus assembly Cpx signaling pathway, periplasmic inhibitor zinc-resistance associated protein

Name: tol-pal system protein YbgF
Description: Mediates coordination of peptidoglycan synthesis and outer membrane constriction during cell division

Name: chaperonin GroEL
Description: Prevents misfolding and promotes the refolding and proper assembly of unfolded polypeptides generated under stress conditions

Name: co-chaperone GroES
Description: Binds to Cpn60 in the presence of Mg-ATP and suppresses the ATPase activity of the latter

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L19
Description: This protein is located at the 30S-50S ribosomal subunit interface and may play a role in the structure and function of the aminoacyl-tRNA binding site

Name: tRNA (guanosine(37)-N1)-methyltransferase TrmD
Description: Belongs to the RNA methyltransferase TrmD family

Name: ribosome maturation factor RimM
Description: An accessory protein needed during the final step in the assembly of 30S ribosomal subunit, possibly for assembly of the head region. Probably interacts with S19. Essential for efficient processing of 16S rRNA. May be needed both before and after RbfA during the maturation of 16S rRNA. It has affinity for free ribosomal 30S subunits but not for 70S ribosomes

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S16
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bS16 family

Name: signal recognition particle protein
Description: Involved in targeting and insertion of nascent membrane proteins into the cytoplasmic membrane. Binds to the hydrophobic signal sequence of the ribosome-nascent chain (RNC) as it emerges from the ribosomes. The SRP-RNC complex is then targeted to the cytoplasmic membrane where it interacts with the SRP receptor FtsY. Interaction with FtsY leads to the transfer of the RNC complex to the Sec translocase for insertion into the membrane, the hydrolysis of GTP by both Ffh and FtsY, and the dissociation of the SRP-FtsY complex into the individual components

Name: glutamine-hydrolyzing GMP synthase
Description: Catalyzes the synthesis of GMP from XMP

Name: Inosine-5'-monophosphate dehydrogenase
Description: Catalyzes the conversion of inosine 5'-phosphate (IMP) to xanthosine 5'-phosphate (XMP), the first committed and rate- limiting step in the de novo synthesis of guanine nucleotides, and therefore plays an important role in the regulation of cell growth

Name: outer membrane protein assembly factor BamB
product: outer membrane protein assembly factor BamB
Description: Part of the outer membrane protein assembly complex, which is involved in assembly and insertion of beta-barrel proteins into the outer membrane

Name: type IV pilus biogenesis/stability protein PilW
product: type IV pilus biogenesis/stability protein PilW

Name: nucleoside-diphosphate kinase
Description: Major role in the synthesis of nucleoside triphosphates other than ATP. The ATP gamma phosphate is transferred to the NDP beta phosphate via a ping-pong mechanism, using a phosphorylated active-site intermediate

Name: Fe-S cluster assembly transcriptional regulator IscR
product: Fe-S cluster assembly transcriptional regulator IscR
Description: Regulates the transcription of several operons and genes involved in the biogenesis of Fe-S clusters and Fe-S-containing proteins

Name: amino acid ABC transporter substrate-binding protein
product: amino acid ABC transporter substrate-binding protein
Description: Amino acid ABC transporter substrate-binding protein

Name: heme o synthase
Description: Converts heme B (protoheme IX) to heme O by substitution of the vinyl group on carbon 2 of heme B porphyrin ring with a hydroxyethyl farnesyl side group

Name: cytochrome o ubiquinol oxidase subunit IV
product: cytochrome o ubiquinol oxidase subunit IV

Name: nitric oxide reductase transcriptional regulator NorR
product: nitric oxide reductase transcriptional regulator NorR

Name: Obg family GTPase CgtA
Description: An essential GTPase which binds GTP, GDP and possibly (p)ppGpp with moderate affinity, with high nucleotide exchange rates and a fairly low GTP hydrolysis rate. Plays a role in control of the cell cycle, stress response, ribosome biogenesis and in those bacteria that undergo differentiation, in morphogenesis control

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L27
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bL27 family

Name: protein-methionine-sulfoxide reductase catalytic subunit MsrP
Description: Part of the MsrPQ system that repairs oxidized periplasmic proteins containing methionine sulfoxide residues (Met-O), using respiratory chain electrons. Thus protects these proteins from oxidative-stress damage caused by reactive species of oxygen and chlorine generated by the host defense mechanisms. MsrPQ is essential for the maintenance of envelope integrity under bleach stress, rescuing a wide series of structurally unrelated periplasmic proteins from methionine oxidation. The catalytic subunit MsrP is non-stereospecific, being able to reduce both (R-) and (S-) diastereoisomers of methionine sulfoxide

Name: CDP-diacylglycerol--serine O-phosphatidyltransferase
Description: Belongs to the CDP-alcohol phosphatidyltransferase class-I family

Name: RNA polymerase-binding protein DksA
Description: Transcription factor that acts by binding directly to the RNA polymerase (RNAP). Required for negative regulation of rRNA expression and positive regulation of several amino acid biosynthesis promoters. Also required for regulation of fis expression

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S15
Description: Forms an intersubunit bridge (bridge B4) with the 23S rRNA of the 50S subunit in the ribosome

Name: tRNA pseudouridine(55) synthase TruB
Description: Responsible for synthesis of pseudouridine from uracil- 55 in the psi GC loop of transfer RNAs

Name: 30S ribosome-binding factor RbfA
Description: One of several proteins that assist in the late maturation steps of the functional core of the 30S ribosomal subunit. Associates with free 30S ribosomal subunits (but not with 30S subunits that are part of 70S ribosomes or polysomes). Required for efficient processing of 16S rRNA. May interact with the 5'-terminal helix region of 16S rRNA

Name: translation initiation factor IF-2
Description: One of the essential components for the initiation of protein synthesis. Protects formylmethionyl-tRNA from spontaneous hydrolysis and promotes its binding to the 30S ribosomal subunits. Also involved in the hydrolysis of GTP during the formation of the 70S ribosomal complex

Name: ribosome maturation factor RimP
Description: Required for maturation of 30S ribosomal subunits

Name: nucleotide exchange factor GrpE
Description: Participates actively in the response to hyperosmotic and heat shock by preventing the aggregation of stress-denatured proteins, in association with DnaK and GrpE. It is the nucleotide exchange factor for DnaK and may function as a thermosensor. Unfolded proteins bind initially to DnaJ

Name: DNA repair protein RecN
Description: May be involved in recombinational repair of damaged DNA

Name: DNA topoisomerase (ATP-hydrolyzing)
Description: A type II topoisomerase that negatively supercoils closed circular double-stranded (ds) DNA in an ATP-dependent manner to modulate DNA topology and maintain chromosomes in an underwound state. Negative supercoiling favors strand separation, and DNA replication, transcription, recombination and repair, all of which involve strand separation. Also able to catalyze the interconversion of other topological isomers of dsDNA rings, including catenanes and knotted rings. Type II topoisomerases break and join 2 DNA strands simultaneously in an ATP-dependent manner

Name: Serine hydroxymethyltransferase 1
Description: Catalyzes the reversible interconversion of serine and glycine with tetrahydrofolate (THF) serving as the one-carbon carrier. This reaction serves as the major source of one-carbon groups required for the biosynthesis of purines, thymidylate, methionine, and other important biomolecules. Also exhibits THF- independent aldolase activity toward beta-hydroxyamino acids, producing glycine and aldehydes, via a retro-aldol mechanism

Name: aldehyde oxidase
Description: Aldehyde oxidase and xanthine dehydrogenase, a/b hammerhead domain

Name: ligand-gated channel
Description: Secretin and TonB N terminus short domain

Name: divalent metal cation transporter FieF
Description: Belongs to the cation diffusion facilitator (CDF) transporter (TC 2.A.4) family

Name: septal ring lytic transglycosylase RlpA family lipoprotein
product: septal ring lytic transglycosylase RlpA family lipoprotein
Description: Lytic transglycosylase with a strong preference for naked glycan strands that lack stem peptides

Name: penicillin-binding protein 2
Description: Catalyzes cross-linking of the peptidoglycan cell wall

Name: nicotinate-nucleotide adenylyltransferase
Description: Catalyzes the reversible adenylation of nicotinate mononucleotide (NaMN) to nicotinic acid adenine dinucleotide (NaAD)

Name: Gamma-glutamyl phosphate reductase
Description: Catalyzes the NADPH-dependent reduction of L-glutamate 5-phosphate into L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde and phosphate. The product spontaneously undergoes cyclization to form 1-pyrroline-5- carboxylate

Name: inorganic diphosphatase
Description: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of inorganic pyrophosphate (PPi) forming two phosphate ions

Name: exodeoxyribonuclease VII small subunit
Description: Bidirectionally degrades single-stranded DNA into large acid-insoluble oligonucleotides, which are then degraded further into small acid-soluble oligonucleotides

Name: (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate synthase
Description: Belongs to the FPP GGPP synthase family

Name: 1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate synthase
Description: Catalyzes the acyloin condensation reaction between C atoms 2 and 3 of pyruvate and glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate to yield 1-deoxy-D-xylulose-5-phosphate (DXP)

Name: transcriptional regulator NrdR
Description: Negatively regulates transcription of bacterial ribonucleotide reductase nrd genes and operons by binding to NrdR- boxes

Name: cardiolipin synthase ClsB
Description: Catalyzes the phosphatidyl group transfer from one phosphatidylglycerol molecule to another to form cardiolipin (CL) (diphosphatidylglycerol) and glycerol

Name: Bacterioferritin
Description: Iron-storage protein, whose ferroxidase center binds Fe(2 ) ions, oxidizes them by dioxygen to Fe(3 ), and participates in the subsequent Fe(3 ) oxide mineral core formation within the central cavity of the protein complex

Name: preprotein translocase subunit SecY
Description: The central subunit of the protein translocation channel SecYEG. Consists of two halves formed by TMs 1-5 and 6-10. These two domains form a lateral gate at the front which open onto the bilayer between TMs 2 and 7, and are clamped together by SecE at the back. The channel is closed by both a pore ring composed of hydrophobic SecY resides and a short helix (helix 2A) on the extracellular side of the membrane which forms a plug. The plug probably moves laterally to allow the channel to open. The ring and the pore may move independently

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S14
Description: Binds 16S rRNA, required for the assembly of 30S particles and may also be responsible for determining the conformation of the 16S rRNA at the A site

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S10
Description: Involved in the binding of tRNA to the ribosomes

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S12
Description: Interacts with and stabilizes bases of the 16S rRNA that are involved in tRNA selection in the A site and with the mRNA backbone. Located at the interface of the 30S and 50S subunits, it traverses the body of the 30S subunit contacting proteins on the other side and probably holding the rRNA structure together. The combined cluster of proteins S8, S12 and S17 appears to hold together the shoulder and platform of the 30S subunit

Name: DNA-directed RNA polymerase subunit beta'
Description: DNA-dependent RNA polymerase catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates

Name: DNA-directed RNA polymerase subunit beta
Description: DNA-dependent RNA polymerase catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L7/L12
Description: Forms part of the ribosomal stalk which helps the ribosome interact with GTP-bound translation factors. Is thus essential for accurate translation

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L10
Description: Forms part of the ribosomal stalk, playing a central role in the interaction of the ribosome with GTP-bound translation factors

Name: transcription termination/antitermination protein NusG
Description: Participates in transcription elongation, termination and antitermination

Name: preprotein translocase subunit SecE
Description: Essential subunit of the Sec protein translocation channel SecYEG. Clamps together the 2 halves of SecY. May contact the channel plug during translocation

Name: N-acetyl-gamma-glutamyl-phosphate reductase
Description: Catalyzes the NADPH-dependent reduction of N-acetyl-5- glutamyl phosphate to yield N-acetyl-L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde

Name: 16S rRNA (adenine(1518)-N(6)/adenine(1519)-N(6))-dimethyltransferase RsmA
Description: Specifically dimethylates two adjacent adenosines (A1518 and A1519) in the loop of a conserved hairpin near the 3'-end of 16S rRNA in the 30S particle. May play a critical role in biogenesis of 30S subunits

Name: 30S ribosomal protein S21
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bS21 family

Name: L-carnitine dehydrogenase
Description: Catalyzes the NAD( )-dependent oxidation of L-carnitine to 3-dehydrocarnitine

Name: transketolase
Description: Catalyzes the transfer of a two-carbon ketol group from a ketose donor to an aldose acceptor, via a covalent intermediate with the cofactor thiamine pyrophosphate

Name: DEAD/DEAH box helicase
Description: DEAD-box RNA helicase involved in ribosome assembly. Has RNA-dependent ATPase activity and unwinds double-stranded RNA

Name: phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase
Description: Belongs to the D-isomer specific 2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase family

Name: transcription termination factor Rho
Description: Facilitates transcription termination by a mechanism that involves Rho binding to the nascent RNA, activation of Rho's RNA-dependent ATPase activity, and release of the mRNA from the DNA template

Name: 50S ribosomal protein L28
Description: Belongs to the bacterial ribosomal protein bL28 family

Name: dUTP diphosphatase
Description: This enzyme is involved in nucleotide metabolism it produces dUMP, the immediate precursor of thymidine nucleotides and it decreases the intracellular concentration of dUTP so that uracil cannot be incorporated into DNA

Name: ABC transporter ATP-binding protein
Description: P-loop containing region of AAA domain

Name: type VI secretion system membrane subunit TssM
product: type VI secretion system membrane subunit TssM

Name: DotU family type VI secretion system protein
product: DotU family type VI secretion system protein
Description: Type VI secretion system protein DotU

product: type VI secretion system baseplate subunit TssK

product: type VI secretion system protein TssA

product: type VI secretion system tubule-forming protein VipA

product: type VI secretion system tubule-forming protein VipB

product: type VI secretion system tube protein Hcp

product: type VI secretion system baseplate subunit TssE

product: type VI secretion system baseplate subunit TssF

product: type VI secretion system baseplate subunit TssG

Name: type VI secretion system ATPase TssH
product: type VI secretion system ATPase TssH
Description: C-terminal, D2-small domain, of ClpB protein

Name: type VI secretion system tip protein VgrG
product: type VI secretion system tip protein VgrG

Name: GlsB/YeaQ/YmgE family stress response membrane protein
product: GlsB/YeaQ/YmgE family stress response membrane protein

Name: glutamine--fructose-6-phosphate transaminase (isomerizing)
Description: Catalyzes the first step in hexosamine metabolism, converting fructose-6P into glucosamine-6P using glutamine as a nitrogen source

Name: F0F1 ATP synthase subunit epsilon
Description: Produces ATP from ADP in the presence of a proton gradient across the membrane

Name: F0F1 ATP synthase subunit beta
Description: Produces ATP from ADP in the presence of a proton gradient across the membrane. The catalytic sites are hosted primarily by the beta subunits

Name: F0F1 ATP synthase subunit alpha
Description: Produces ATP from ADP in the presence of a proton gradient across the membrane. The alpha chain is a regulatory subunit

Name: F0F1 ATP synthase subunit C
Description: F(1)F(0) ATP synthase produces ATP from ADP in the presence of a proton or sodium gradient. F-type ATPases consist of two structural domains, F(1) containing the extramembraneous catalytic core and F(0) containing the membrane proton channel, linked together by a central stalk and a peripheral stalk. During catalysis, ATP synthesis in the catalytic domain of F(1) is coupled via a rotary mechanism of the central stalk subunits to proton translocation

Name: F0F1 ATP synthase subunit A
Description: it plays a direct role in the translocation of protons across the membrane

Name: RNA polymerase subunit sigma
Description: Belongs to the sigma-70 factor family. ECF subfamily

Name: membrane protein insertase YidC
Description: Required for the insertion and or proper folding and or complex formation of integral membrane proteins into the membrane. Involved in integration of membrane proteins that insert both dependently and independently of the Sec translocase complex, as well as at least some lipoproteins. Aids folding of multispanning membrane proteins
